      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW JASTA (1) charged out of the boxes with a fast early split and led throughout to score when a 3 length winner (21.83) over 390m at Shepparton. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. ANCHOR CRANKER (4) got a clear run and led until the final stages when third and beaten 1.75 lengths (23.53) at this track in a Grade 5 over 410m. Will give a great sight again. IS HE LUCKY (7) crossed over from out wide last start before finishing second (23.42) at this track in a Grade 5 over 410m. Has a strong record out of this box with four wins and three minor placings from nine starts. Nicely placed to grab a well-deserved win. EMPTY YOUR MIND (2) looks a top-three hope after a break.",
